If the evas_close functions are called on exit, it dumps core.
------------------------------------------------------------------------
With SDL_TIMER zoomed in on X, the CPU load makes it unable to
signal results and the display gets screwed.
------------------------------------------------------------------------
If you zoom in too much, the graphic turns upside down and zooms in.
Zoom by 2: centre=622.254 range=11.3137 min_freq=55 max_freq=7040
Zoom by 2: centre=622.254 range=5.65685 min_freq=110 max_freq=3520
Zoom by 2: centre=622.254 range=2.82843 min_freq=220 max_freq=1760
Zoom by 2: centre=622.254 range=1.41421 min_freq=440 max_freq=880
Zoom by 2: centre=622.254 range=0.707107 min_freq=880 max_freq=440 <--
min_freq > max_freq... and it works!
------------------------------------------------------------------------
When zoomed into X axis, Left and Right should move less.
------------------------------------------------------------------------
When scrolling screenfuls, it calculates loads of stuff that's
already off-screen.
------------------------------------------------------------------------
If you X-zoom and X-zoom again before it's finished repainting, it dumps core.
------------------------------------------------------------------------
